About company:

Austin Capital Trust Company, LLC is a Nevada-chartered trust company that offers a range of financial services including trust and custody, retirement plan services, turnkey asset management, and a unified managed household platform.

Revenue: $5 Million

Website: https://www.austincapitaltrust.com
info
Our Summary:

This network also contains databases belonging to another company, FinTech Automation, which is linked to the founders and executives of published company. We want to highlight that personal data at both organizations is stored almost everywhere on file servers, systems logs, product folders, technical and personal folders, which is a violation of data protection rules. This is grounds for the Attorney General and the Federal Trade Commission to investigate this breach, as the organization's customers' personal and financial files are stored without any protection in accordance with regulations or even basic compliance standards. There is no encryption, no access separation, no data transfer monitoring, nothing reasonable.

Description:

- 500 GB of accessible data.
- Data from the company's file server.
- Network user data.
- Large amounts of personal data of all kinds.
- Medical and financial data.
- Data from Fintech Automation.
- Data from Mora Law.
- Business and operational data, structured financial data.
- System logs.

info
Our Summary:

This company was notified through 5 various channels with evidence of the network breach. Yet each time, its representatives claimed that they had not received any messages, which is a lie. Given the quality of the data we have, we strongly recommend filing a complaint with the New York State Attorney General's Office and preparing for a class action lawsuit on behalf of customers whose data this company cared so little about that it did not even contact them to fully validate the leak. All customer and contractor contacts will be provided here shortly. In the meantime, you can explore the data tree to check the list of files we have.
